<article id="post-75" class="post-75 page type-page status-publish hentry">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">Welcome to Parktimes</h1>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	<div class="entry-content">
		
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="http://parktimes.com/sections/parkwide/flagtower.jpg"><img decoding="async" src="http://parktimes.com/sections/parkwide/flagtower.jpg" alt=""/></a></figure>



<p>     Welcome to Parktimes.com, covering the history of <em>Six Flags Over Texas</em>. The park is the first, and oldest, in the Six Flags theme parks&#8217; chain of amusement parks. Opening in 1961, six years after Disneyland, the park was one of a hand-full of new theme parks which opened in the late 50&#8217;s and early 60&#8217;s. With the exception of Disneyland and Six Flags Over Texas, the others were all closed or bankrupt within a few seasons. Six Flags Over Texas flourished and expanded, and was followed by Six Flags Over Georgia and Six Flags Over Mid-America (now Six Flags St. Louis). The following pages detail the highlights and changes that have entertained millions of guests.</p>



<p><strong>Navigation</strong></p>



<p>Particular articles can be located using the [Search] field.</p>



<p>You can also navigate the site using the menu system which divides the site based on the parks physical sections. </p>



<p>In addition, you can use the &#8220;category&#8221; feature to list articles based on common themes.</p>



<p> Submitted&nbsp;on&nbsp;Wed, 06/22/2016 &#8211; 20:09 </p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	
</article><!-- #post-75 -->

	</main><!-- .site-main -->

	
</div><!-- .content-area -->


